<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Some problems still remain</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:19 a.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Some problems still remain<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1522" TARGET=_self>Some problems still remain</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> #2 If you use a racial hiding skill you cannot tell if you have

<BR>&gt; succeeded.
<P>To my knowledge, if you are successfull, you will not simply "disappear" from the game. Anyone who already has sight of you will keep seeing you. New people who come across you will not see you.
<P>But then, I've never played a character with hiding skills so I could be completely wrong.
<P>&gt; #4 Red PvP players that die to a mob are still lootable by other
<BR>&gt; players, even though you receive a message that you cannot loot
<BR>&gt; this player, you are still able to remove an item from their
<BR>&gt; inventory as well as all of their coins. This looting condition
<BR>&gt; should only be in effect when another red PvP player has done a
<BR>&gt; majority of the overall damage to that player.
<P>This is one of the most glaring bugs which remain. Hopefully, the dev team will find time to deal with it in a very short time. If new features start appearing on the nonPvP servers before this is fixed, scream. Loudly.
<P>Until then, they have their hands full with a brand spankin' new retail release.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
